    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent | </hi>(<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>July 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1880</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have much pleasure in enclosing 25£ for your Scientific Fund in Birmingham—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi></note>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">On 19 July 1880, CD recorded a payment of £25 to ‘Birm Sc Fund’ under ‘Gifts [and] Annual Subscriptions’ in his Classed account books (Down House MS). For more on the fund, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12659.xml">letter to Lawson Tait, 16 July [1880]</ref> and n. 3.</note>   
        </div>
    
